We found that three local places were mentioned in the first {Domesday Book} and we decided to check their present populations to see how much bigger they had grown.When they were put into the first {Domesday Book}they had about 100 people between them. That is an average population of 33. We looked at the 1981 Census.
Population.(1981) Aston Juxta Mondrum. Then 33. Now 173. Pool Then 33. Now 109. Worleston. Then 33. Now 270.
Some of these people still work on farms like their ancestors did, but a lot now go into Crewe to work at Rolls Royce or at British Rail Engineering. They aren't all that much bigger 800 years after {Domesday. }
